---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const siteName = import.meta.env.PUBLIC_SITE_NAME ?? "PricingNest";
---
<BaseLayout
  title={`API Pricing Model (How to Price per 1k Calls) | ${siteName}`}
  description="A practical model for API pricing: estimate unit cost, set a margin-safe price, and design tiers and minimums."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>API pricing model</h1>
    <p>Price APIs with a simple model: unit cost + fixed overhead + target gross margin, then wrap it in tiers and minimums.</p>
  </section>

  <div class="grid">
    <article class="card col8">
      <h2>Step 1: estimate the cost per 1k calls</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>Compute and data processing per call.</li>
        <li>Vendor APIs/LLMs per call (if any).</li>
        <li>Shared overhead you want to recover (support, tooling) via a platform minimum.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">Step 2: set a target margin</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>Pick a margin range based on your category and cost structure.</li>
        <li>Model p50 vs p90 usage so heavy customers are still profitable.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">Step 3: design tiers + minimums</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>Use a minimum platform fee to cover baseline costs and reduce small noisy accounts.</li>
        <li>Use tiers to reduce bill shock and simplify buyer expectations.</li>
        <li>Publish examples (typical, heavy) to make bills predictable.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">Tools to use</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/api-pricing-calculator/">API pricing calculator</a></li>
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/usage-based-pricing-calculator/">Usage-based pricing calculator</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/usage-based-pricing-examples/">Usage pricing examples</a></li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <aside class="card col4">
      <h2>Related</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li><a href="/glossary/usage-based-pricing/">Glossary: usage-based pricing</a></li>
        <li><a href="/glossary/gross-margin/">Glossary: gross margin</a></li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

